data.title: Important center of the community
data.text: Marshall Center has been around forever.  My husband used to have swimming lessons here now our kids have lessons here, have gone to preschool here, I workout here occasionally.  We love touring the gardens through the seasons and learning different tricks from the different gardeners. An integral part of our community.

data.title: run down
data.text: This place is really for senior citizens. They have a pool but old. Kids would get board fast. Would go with kids.

data.title: Good work out room and pool
data.text: We joined the health club to avoid the major expenses of a larger national brand.  We found that the costs are the same or more.  However, it is very close to our house, the facilities are good and there always seems to be something happening down there.

data.title: Great pool
data.text: The Marshall Community Center is ran by the City of Vancouver Parks Department.  It has a full gym with a variety of exercise machines.  The center offers a variety of exercise classes and, a full sized gym of sports In addition there is an Olympic size pool.  The pool is very popular providing many different water exercise classes and swim times for individuals and families

data.title: classes things to do
data.text: Nice senior area and young kids. Swimming, small rock wall. Track to walk on and classes that you can take

data.title: Fun Family Spot
data.text: A great community center with wonderful volunteers.  Just about something for our entire family.  Love the nice deep water pool!
